ation when initializing tracing\n\n5. **Service Discovery Plugins**:\n   - Kubernetes SD (`discovery/kubernetes/kubernetes.go`, line 112): `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - Consul SD (checked via config_test.go): Uses HTTPClientConfig with TLSConfig\n   - Triton SD (`discovery/triton/triton.go`, line 69): `TLSConfig config.TLSConfig`\n   - OpenStack SD (`discovery/openstack/openstack.go`, line 65): `TLSConfig config.TLSConfig`\n   - HTTP SD (`discovery/http/http.go`, line 57): `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - Multiple other discovery plugins follow the same pattern\n\n## Server-Side TLS Configuration\n\n**Web Server TLS** (`web/web.go`, lines 671-719):\n- The Run method uses toolkit_web.ServeMultiple with webConfig parameter\n- The webConfig file specifies TLS settings (cert_file, key_file) for the HTTP server\n- This is configured through the --web.config.file flag in `cmd/prometheus/main.go`\n- The toolkit_web.ServeMultiple handles establishing TLS listeners\n\n## TLS Validation\n\n**promtool Configuration Validation** (`cmd/promtool/main.go`, lines 760-780):\n- checkTLSConfig function validates that cert and key files are paired correctly\n- Performs file existence checks when not in syntax-only mode\n- Applied to scrape config TLS validation (line 679)\n- Applied to service discovery TLS validation (line 686 for Kubernetes, line 687 for other SDs)\n- CheckWebConfig function (line 607) validates the web server TLS configuration\n\n## Standardized HTTP Transport Configuration\n\nIn `config/http_config.go` (lines 136-182), NewRoundTripperFromConfig:\n- Creates http.Transport with TLSClientConfig set from NewTLSConfig\n- Configures TLS handshake timeout (line 149)\n- Handles automatic CA file reloading via tlsRoundTripper for certificate rotation\n- Applies to all HTTP clients: scrape targets, remote write/read, tracing, and service discovery\n\n## Key TLS Identifiers Referenced\n\n- TLSConfig: The configuration struct (prometheus-common)\n- NewTLSConfig: Factory function converting TLSConfig to crypto/tls.Config (prometheus-common)\n- HTTPClientConfig: Wrapper struct containing TLSConfig for HTTP clients\n- NewClientFromConfig: Creates HTTP clients with TLS support\n- NewRoundTripperFromConfig: Creates HTTP transport with TLS\n- ServeMultiple: Toolkit function for server-side TLS setup\n- checkTLSConfig: Validation function in promtool\n\nThis architecture ensures TLS is consistently enforced across all external interfaces: scrape targets, remote storage endpoints, tracing exporters, service discovery API calls, and the web server itself."
