ntConfig config.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - Write clients created in `storage/remote/client.go` (line 188)\n   - NewClientFromConfig applies the TLS configuration\n\n3. **Remote Read Endpoints** (`config/config.go`, lines 1211-1212):\n   - RemoteReadConfig contains `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - Read clients created in `storage/remote/client.go` (line 159)\n   - Same TLS pattern as remote write\n\n4. **Tracing Exporters** (`config/config.go`, lines 920-929):\n   - TracingConfig contains `TLSConfig config.TLSConfig` (line 925)\n   - Tracing endpoints use NewTLSConfig in `tracing/tracing.go` (lines 189, 222)\n   - Validates TLS configuration when initializing tracing\n\n5. **Service Discovery Plugins**:\n   - Kubernetes SD (`discovery/kubernetes/kubernetes.go`, line 112): `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - Consul SD (checked via config_test.go): Uses HTTPClientConfig with TLSConfig\n   - Triton SD (`discovery/triton/triton.go`, line 69): `TLSConfig config.TLSConfig`\n   - OpenStack SD (`discovery/openstack/openstack.go`, line 65): `TLSConfig config.TLSConfig`\n   - HTTP SD (`discovery/http/http.go`, line 57): `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig`\n   - Multiple other discovery plugins follow the same pattern\n\n## Server-Side TLS Configuration\n\n**Web Server TLS** (`web/web.go`, lines 671-719):\n- The Run method uses toolkit_web.ServeMultiple with webConfig parameter\n- The webConfig file specifies TLS settings (cert_file, key_file) for the HTTP server\n- This is configured through the --web.config.file flag in `cmd/prometheus/main.go`\n- The toolkit_web.ServeMultiple handles establishing TLS listeners\n\n## TLS Validation\n\n**promtool Configuration Validation** (`cmd/promtool/main.go`, lines 760-780):\n- checkTLSConfig function validates that cert and key files are paired correctly\n- Performs file existence checks when not in syntax-only mode\n- Applied to scrape config TLS validation (line 679)\n- Applied to service discovery TLS 